Mozambican rebel leader Afonso Dhlakama announced Tuesday a two-month ceasefire in the rumbling conflict between Renamo and the government, extending a week-long truce in a move welcomed by the president.&#8220;There have been some minor incidents, but the seven-day truce went well, so I announce the extension of the truce for 60 days, until March 4,&#8221; Dhlakama said in a telephone press conference.-AFP